<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910826-0071</DOCNO><DOCID>910826-0071.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Sharper Image Corp.:   Retailer's Deficit Widened   In Second Quarter From '90</HL><DATE>08/26/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A5</SO><CO>   SHRP</CO><MS>CONSUMER CYCLICAL (CYC)</MS><IN>EARNINGS (ERN)OTHER SPECIALTY RETAILERS OF LIMITED PRODUCT LINES (OTS)ALL SPECIALTY RETAILERS (RTS)</IN><NS>EARNINGS (ERN)</NS><RE>CALIFORNIA (CA)NORTH AMERICA (NME)PACIFIC RIM (PRM)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   Blaming the &quot;continuing recession,&quot; Sharper Image Corp.reported a loss for its second quarter.   The specialty retailer said in San Francisco it had a lossof $2.4 million, or 29 cents a share, for the quarter endedJuly 31, compared with a year-earlier loss of $1.6 million,or 19 cents a share. Revenue fell 27% to $30.2 million from$41.2 million.</LP><TEXT>   In the first six months, Sharper Image had a net loss of$5.9 million, or 72 cents a share, compared with a year-agoloss of $3 million, or 36 cents a share. Revenue fell 27% to$55.4 million from $75.8 million.</TEXT></DOC>